    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="87"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.2315/82</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 193</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I enclose for your confidential information an
                    extract from a despatch from the American Minister at Bogotá,<note n="86"
                        xml:id="d87fn86">See despatch No. 113, <ref target="#pg_81">p.
                        81</ref>.</note> reporting a recent conversation with the President of
                    Colombia, in which he requested that this Government would use its good offices
                    with the Government of Peru to induce it to continue the negotiations with
                    Colombia so that a satisfactory agreement might be reached regarding the
                    disputed boundary between the two countries.</p>
                <p>You may use your good offices with this end in view, orally and informally
                    discussing the matter with the Peruvian Minister of Foreign Relations.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
